<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id6c760e68-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e" identifier="/us/usc/t33/s3025"><num value="3025">§ 3025.</num><heading> Length of service for promotion purposes</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id6c760e69-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e" identifier="/us/usc/t33/s3025/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> General rule</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Each officer shall be assumed to have, for promotion purposes, at least the same length of service as any other officer below that officer on the lineal list.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id6c760e6a-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e" identifier="/us/usc/t33/s3025/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Exception</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Notwithstanding subsection (a), an officer who has lost numbers shall be assumed to have, for promotion purposes, no greater service than the officer next above such officer in such officer’s new position on the lineal list.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id6c760e6b-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e">(<ref href="/us/pl/107/372/tII/s225">Pub. L. 107–372, title II, § 225</ref>, <date date="2002-12-19">Dec. 19, 2002</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/116/3085">116 Stat. 3085</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id6c760e6c-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id6c760e6d-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="priorProvisions" id="id6c760e6e-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Prior Provisions</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Provisions similar to those in this section were contained in <ref href="/us/usc/t33/s853f">section 853f of this title</ref> prior to repeal by <ref href="/us/pl/107/372">Pub. L. 107–372</ref>.</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
